  "commentary": "With SPX at 7015 sitting just below the massive +20.17B gamma wall at 7025, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that level while providing stabilizing buying support on dips toward the 7000 (+16.67B) and 7010 (+7.36B) walls. The PIN regime with 148B in total positive GEX creates a powerful mean-reversion environment, especially with the GEX flip far below at 6859, meaning dealers will mechanically fade moves in both directions. Key resistance remains the 7025 max gamma strike where dealer selling pressure peaks, while the 7000-7010 zone should act as a magnet for any weakness.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 7000-7025 with dealers capping upside moves.",
